{
  "doc_id": "19069",
  "text": "In the case when M is a regular covering of M , Elworthy [CITATION_1] used stochastic differential equations to give a proof of the fact that M satisfies (SI) if and only if M satisfies (SI). Pigola and Setti [CITATION_2] asked for a deterministic proof of this fact. By Theorem 5.3, we may provide an affirmative answer to their question. where the last equality follows from the co-area formula. The theorem is a direct consequence of the above equality.",
